+# ADR 0002 — Currency-aware banker's rounding utility
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-05-27
+- **Deciders:** Solution Architect
+- **Area:** `src/features/ledger/lib` (money arithmetic)
+- **Relates to:** ADR 0001 (input-boundary validation for monetary amounts)
+
+## Context
+
+ADR 0001 established a single input-boundary validator (`amount.ts`) and
+canonicalized USD amounts to two decimals via a private `roundToCents`, which
+uses `Math.round` — i.e. **round-half-up**. It also recorded a residual risk:
+"large sums across many rows can still accumulate sub-cent drift in aggregates."
+Half-up rounding has a systematic upward bias because every exact-half tie
+rounds the same direction; over many rows this skews totals (`computeSDE`,
+balances, tax reserves).
+
+Two further gaps:
+
+- **No currency-awareness.** `roundToCents` hard-codes 2 decimal places. The
+  ledger is USD-only today (`lib/format.ts:1-6`), but zero-decimal (JPY) and
+  three-decimal (BHD/KWD) currencies round to different minor units, and the
+  validator's cents assumption would be wrong for them.
+- **No reusable rounding primitive.** `roundToCents` is private to `amount.ts`;
+  any other module needing to round money would re-implement it.
+
+Inspected: `ledger/lib/amount.ts` (`roundToCents`, `hasAtMostCents`),
+`ledger/lib/amount.test.ts`, `ledger/types.ts` (`Transaction.amount: number`),
+`lib/format.ts` (USD `Intl.NumberFormat`, 2dp), `ledger/index.ts` (barrel),
+`docs/adr/0001`.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add `src/features/ledger/lib/round.ts` — a pure, currency-aware rounding
+primitive using **banker's rounding (round-half-to-even)**.
+
+- `roundMoney(value, currency)` rounds `value` to the currency's minor units,
+  breaking exact-half ties toward the even neighbour (0.005 → 0.00, 0.015 →
+  0.02, 2.675 → 2.68). Half-detection uses an epsilon (`1e-9`) because ties are
+  never exactly representable in IEEE-754 (`0.005 * 100 === 0.4999…`); reliable
+  while the scaled magnitude stays within `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER`.
+- `MINOR_UNITS` / `DEFAULT_MINOR_UNITS` / `minorUnits(currency)` resolve decimal
+  digits per ISO-4217 code (USD/EUR…=2, JPY/KRW…=0, BHD/KWD…=3), case-insensitive,
+  unknown codes → 2.
+- **NaN/Infinity-safe = fail-loud:** a non-finite `value` (or non-number, or
+  blank currency) throws `RangeError` rather than silently propagating a corrupt
+  figure into balances — consistent with `amount.ts` rejecting `not-finite`.
+
+This follows the repo convention: co-located, side-effect-free libs exported via
+the feature barrel (`features/ledger/index.ts`). It does **not** change the
+canonical representation (signed 2-decimal `number`) — no consumer churn.
+
+**Why not change `roundToCents` in place / make `amount.ts` call `roundMoney`?**
+Deliberately deferred. `amount.ts`'s current half-up behaviour at the *input
+boundary* is harmless (it canonicalizes a single freshly-parsed magnitude, where
+there is no tie-bias accumulation). Rewiring it now would mean re-validating the
+12 existing boundary tests for a behaviour change with no present consumer. The
+swap is recorded as a follow-up (Task 4) for when an aggregation path actually
+calls into rounding. **Alternative considered — integer-cents representation**
+(per ADR 0001): still rejected for the same reason; `roundMoney` is the
+lighter-weight mitigation for the drift risk ADR 0001 flagged.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- **Positive:** a reusable, tested money-rounding primitive; half-even removes
+  the upward tie-bias for any future aggregation/allocation/split logic;
+  currency-aware ahead of any non-USD support; corrupt (NaN/∞) values fail loud
+  at the arithmetic layer too, not only at input.
+- **Negative / residual risk:** two rounding helpers now coexist (`roundToCents`
+  half-up in `amount.ts`, `roundMoney` half-even). Documented here and bounded by
+  Task 4 to converge them. Epsilon tie-detection degrades above
+  `MAX_SAFE_INTEGER`; out of range for this ledger (per-tx ceiling $1M, ADR 0001).
+- **Carried forward:** when persistence / non-USD support lands, revisit both the
+  integer-cents migration (ADR 0001) and converging `roundToCents` onto
+  `roundMoney`.
+
+## Coverage / verification
+
+- `round.test.ts`: 13 cases — .005/.015/.025 half-even boundary, 2.675 classic
+  case, negative symmetry, JPY (0dp), BHD (3dp), case-insensitive + unknown-code
+  fallback, very-large within safe-integer range, very-small, and the
+  NaN/Infinity/non-number/blank-currency `RangeError` guards.
+- `npm test` → **25/25 pass** (12 amount + 13 round).
+- `tsc --noEmit` clean for the new module (only the pre-existing unrelated
+  `e2e/benchmarks-compare.unit.spec.ts` error from ADR 0001 remains).
+- Exported through `features/ledger/index.ts`.
+
+## Task breakdown
+
+1. **`roundMoney` + currency minor-units table** — pure half-even rounding to a
+   currency's minor units, NaN/∞ fail-loud. *(implemented)* — **3 pts**
+2. **Unit tests for edge cases** — half-even boundary, negative, zero/-0, 0/3-dp
+   currencies, very large/small, non-finite guards. *(implemented)* — **2 pts**
+3. **Barrel export** — surface `roundMoney`/`minorUnits` from
+   `features/ledger/index.ts`. *(implemented)* — **1 pt**
+4. **Converge `roundToCents` → `roundMoney`** *(follow-up, blocked on first
+   aggregation consumer)* — switch `amount.ts` canonicalization to half-even and
+   re-validate the 12 boundary tests. — **2 pts**
+
+**Total: 8 pts — 6 delivered this run, 2 deferred (Task 4).**
