+++ b/CHANGELOG.md
+# Changelog
+
+All notable changes to this project are documented here.
+
+The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
+and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).
+While the project is pre-1.0 (`0.x`), breaking changes increment the **minor** version.
+
+## [Unreleased]
+
+## [0.3.0] - 2026-05-27
+
+Backward-compatible feature release on the ledger money layer. No breaking
+changes since `0.2.0`, so under the pre-1.0 policy this lands as a **minor**.
+
+### Added
+
+- **Currency-aware banker's rounding.** A new reusable money-arithmetic
+  primitive (`roundMoney` / `minorUnits` / `MINOR_UNITS`) rounds a value to any
+  currency's minor units using round-half-to-even (banker's rounding) instead of
+  the half-up convention `amount.ts` uses at the input boundary. Half-even avoids
+  the systematic upward bias half-up introduces when summing many rows (SDE,
+  balances, tax reserves — the sub-cent drift residual risk recorded in ADR
+  0001). Handles zero-decimal (JPY/KRW) and three-decimal (BHD/KWD) currencies;
+  unknown codes default to 2 decimals. Pure and side-effect-free. (ADR 0002)
+- **Ledger amount validation.** Every amount entering the ledger — from an SMS/OCR
+  receipt capture, a forwarded invoice, or a Plaid bank-feed row — is now validated
+  and canonicalized at the input boundary. Amounts are stored as a signed USD value
+  (income positive, expense negative), rounded to cents, and rejected with a
+  user-facing reason if they're blank, non-numeric, zero, over-precise, negative, or
+  above the $1,000,000 per-transaction limit. Rejection messages are written for the
+  SMS reply / review queue (e.g. *"That doesn't look like a dollar amount."*).
+- **Transaction ingest boundary.** A single seam (`ingestTransaction` /
+  `ingestTransactions`) that every amount source will funnel through before a row
+  lands in the ledger: it validates each raw row's amount, projects valid rows into
+  canonical transactions, and collects invalid ones as rejections for the review
+  queue. Prepares the ledger for the live Twilio and Plaid adapters.
+
+## [0.2.0] - 2026-05-27
+
+Pre-1.0 platform migration. This release moves the scaffold onto the current
+major versions of its core framework stack. No product features changed, but
+contributors must update their local toolchain.
+
+### Changed
+
+- **BREAKING — Next.js 14 → 16.** The App Router scaffold now runs on Next.js 16.
+  Local environments and CI must reinstall dependencies; older Next.js builds are
+  no longer supported.
+- **BREAKING — React 18 → 19.** Upgraded React and React DOM to 19. Closes 14 known
+  CVEs carried by the previous framework versions.
+- **BREAKING — Tailwind CSS 3 → 4.** Adopts the new Oxide engine and the
+  `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin. PostCSS config and `globals.css` were updated to
+  the v4 setup.
+- **BREAKING — TypeScript 5 → 6 and ESLint 9 → 10.** Strict typecheck and the flat
+  ESLint config now target the new majors (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks` 7,
+  `@types/node` 25).
+- Updated the Google Gemini SDK (`@google/generative-ai`) to 0.24.
+
+### Fixed
+
+- Simplified the customer side-panel portal mount: removed the redundant
+  `useEffect`/`mounted` hydration gate in favor of a direct `typeof document`
+  guard, avoiding an unnecessary client re-render under Tailwind 4.
+

