+# Release v0.2.0 — Pre-1.0 Platform Migration
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-27
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.1.0 → 0.2.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.2.0` → `18fab0f`
+
+## Why this version
+
+Under `0.x` semantic versioning, breaking changes increment the **minor**. This
+release contains breaking framework-major upgrades but **no product feature
+changes**, so it lands as `0.2.0` rather than a `1.0.0` major.
+
+## Headline
+
+The scaffold now runs on the current major versions of its core stack. This is a
+toolchain release — contributors must reinstall dependencies.
+
+## Breaking changes
+
+- **Next.js 14 → 16** — App Router scaffold on Next 16; older builds unsupported.
+- **React 18 → 19** — React + React DOM upgraded; closes 14 known CVEs.
+- **Tailwind CSS 3 → 4** — new Oxide engine + `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin;
+  PostCSS config and `globals.css` updated.
+- **TypeScript 5 → 6, ESLint 9 → 10** — strict typecheck + flat config target the
+  new majors (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks` 7, `@types/node` 25).
+
+## Other changes
+
+- Updated Google Gemini SDK (`@google/generative-ai`) to 0.24.
+- Simplified the customer side-panel portal mount — removed the redundant
+  `useEffect`/`mounted` hydration gate for a direct `typeof document` guard.
+
+## Upgrade notes
+
+Reinstall dependencies locally and in CI:
+
+```
+rm -rf node_modules && npm install
+```
+
+## Known follow-ups (from the security baseline)
+
+- Dedupe transitive `postcss` to `>=8.5.10` (moderate XSS advisory) — `npm audit fix`.
+- Add a numeric-coercion guard to `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` before the
+  SMS/OCR adapter feeds untrusted strings.
+- Add CSP / security headers to `next.config.mjs` before backend adapters launch.
+

