+# Release v0.3.0 — Ledger Money Layer
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-27
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.2.0 → 0.3.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.3.0` → `b29eeaa` (pending — see Release-integrity gate below)
+
+## Why this version
+
+Backward-compatible feature additions to the ledger, **no breaking changes**
+since `0.2.0`. Under `0.x` semantic versioning a feature release increments the
+**minor**, so this lands as `0.3.0`. The bump is derived from the merged history,
+not guessed: `git log v0.2.0..HEAD` is a single `feat(ledger)` commit
+(`b29eeaa`), plus the validation/ingest feature work staged in the changelog's
+Unreleased section.
+
+## Headline
+
+The ledger gains its money-arithmetic foundation: a currency-aware banker's
+rounding primitive, plus the input-boundary amount validator and the transaction
+ingest seam that future Twilio/Plaid adapters will funnel through.
+
+## What's new
+
+- **Currency-aware banker's rounding** (`roundMoney` / `minorUnits` /
+  `MINOR_UNITS`, ADR 0002). Round-half-to-even to any currency's minor units —
+  zero-decimal (JPY/KRW) and three-decimal (BHD/KWD) included; unknown codes
+  default to 2. Avoids the upward bias half-up introduces when summing many rows
+  (SDE, balances, tax reserves — ADR 0001's sub-cent-drift residual risk). Pure,
+  side-effect-free.
+- **Ledger amount validation** — every amount is validated and canonicalized at
+  the input boundary (signed USD, rounded to cents, rejected with a user-facing
+  reason for blank / non-numeric / zero / over-precise / negative / over-$1M).
+- **Transaction ingest boundary** (`ingestTransaction` / `ingestTransactions`) —
+  the single seam every amount source funnels through, projecting valid rows and
+  collecting rejections for the review queue.
+
+## Bump rationale (auditable)
+
+| Input | Signal | Bump |
+|-------|--------|------|
+| `feat(ledger): currency-aware banker's rounding utility` (`b29eeaa`) | new backward-compatible API | MINOR |
+| Amount validation + ingest boundary (Unreleased) | new backward-compatible APIs | MINOR |
+| Breaking changes since `v0.2.0`? | none | — |
+
+→ Highest applicable bump = **MINOR** → `0.3.0`.
+
+## Release-integrity gate (must clear before publishing the tag)
+
+The committed barrel `src/features/ledger/index.ts` re-exports `./lib/amount`
+and `./lib/ingest`, but those files (`amount.ts`, `amount.test.ts`, `ingest.ts`)
+are **untracked** in the working tree — only `round.ts` / `round.test.ts` are
+committed at `b29eeaa`. Tagging `b29eeaa` as-is would ship a build whose barrel
+imports files absent from history. This is the build-integrity defect already
+owned by Code Review / CI; the `v0.3.0` tag should be cut only after those files
+are committed. Version bump, changelog, and these notes are prepared now; tag
+creation is deferred to that gate.
+
+## Carried-over follow-ups (from the security baseline)
+
+- Transitive `postcss` is already pinned to `^8.5.15` (≥ 8.5.10) in
+  `devDependencies` — the v0.2.0 XSS advisory remediation is in place.
+- Keep ledger secrets (`GEMINI_API_KEY`, `PLAID_SECRET`, `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`,
+  `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`) server-side; never `NEXT_PUBLIC_`-prefix them when the
+  adapters are wired.
+

